    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "The Prophet Muhammad (s) narrated that Adam, after his descent from Paradise, suffered from inner distress and sadness. Allah sent Gabriel to teach him the formula 'la hawla wa la quwwata illa billah' (there is no power nor strength except by Allah). Upon reciting it, Adam's whispering thoughts and grief were relieved. This demonstrates the power of this dhikr formula as a remedy for anxiety and sorrow, established from the very beginning of human history.",
        "key_terms": {
          "الوسوسة": "Whispering, intrusive thoughts; inner distress caused by the self or Satan",
          "الحزن": "Grief, sadness, sorrow",
          "لا حول ولا قوة إلا بالله": "There is no power nor strength except by Allah (la hawla wa la quwwata illa billah); a powerful dhikr formula"
        },
        "seo_question": "What did Gabriel teach Adam to relieve his grief and anxiety?"
